snippet: The explosion, which injured at least two people, came as protest barricades and tents still stand in the central square months after demonstrations that toppled the government.
abstract: Explosion in Kiev, Ukraine, wounds at least two people and ignites fears of new conflict in city; motive for attack is not immediately clear.
lead_paragraph: The explosion, which injured at least two people, came as protest barricades and tents still stand in the central square months after demonstrations that toppled the government.

headline.main: Blast in Ukraine’s Capital Stirs Fears of New Conflict
